The paper deals with width parameters of graphs and matroids, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.DS). The use of games as a tool for studying these parameters suggests a connection to game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions planar subgraphs, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG), and the monotonicity property, which is relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
